Welcome back.

00:44:47.050 --> 00:44:49.590 align:middle line:84%
I'm Lisa Garr, and my
guest is Jean Houston.

00:44:49.590 --> 00:44:52.850 align:middle line:84%
We are exploring
the possible human,

00:44:52.850 --> 00:44:55.230 align:middle line:84%
which is what Jean
basically coined

00:44:55.230 --> 00:44:57.740 align:middle line:84%
this term, the possible
human, if you could.

00:44:57.740 --> 00:45:02.020 align:middle line:84%
Those two words together are
a beautiful combination--

00:45:02.020 --> 00:45:05.080 align:middle line:84%
the possible human-- when we,
at some points in our life,

00:45:05.080 --> 00:45:08.460 align:middle line:84%
lose a lot of
possibility and that

00:45:08.460 --> 00:45:10.670 align:middle line:90%
around our story of possibility.

00:45:10.670 --> 00:45:13.300 align:middle line:90%
So the story is changing for us.

00:45:13.300 --> 00:45:15.060 align:middle line:90%
With whom is it changing?

00:45:15.060 --> 00:45:16.630 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, just
about everybody.

00:45:16.630 --> 00:45:17.887 align:middle line:90%
Give me a category.

00:45:17.887 --> 00:45:19.720 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: We were talking
earlier about women.

00:45:19.720 --> 00:45:20.428 align:middle line:90%
>>HOUSTON: Women.

00:45:20.428 --> 00:45:22.050 align:middle line:90%
All right.

00:45:22.050 --> 00:45:25.540 align:middle line:84%
So I'm in India-- this
is some years ago--

00:45:25.540 --> 00:45:27.860 align:middle line:84%
and I'm in a village,
small village,

00:45:27.860 --> 00:45:30.890 align:middle line:84%
and it has one television
set owned by an old Brahmin

00:45:30.890 --> 00:45:32.800 align:middle line:90%
lady, high caste lady.

00:45:32.800 --> 00:45:35.170 align:middle line:84%
And she has placed
it in the trees.

00:45:35.170 --> 00:45:36.980 align:middle line:84%
And people come
in from the fields

00:45:36.980 --> 00:45:38.460 align:middle line:84%
and they tie up
their water buffalo

00:45:38.460 --> 00:45:43.180 align:middle line:84%
and they come and sit down to
watch the "Ramayana," which

00:45:43.180 --> 00:45:45.990 align:middle line:84%
at this point was every Sunday
and I think 30 episodes.

00:45:45.990 --> 00:45:49.690 align:middle line:90%
It is the core story of India.

00:45:49.690 --> 00:45:51.560 align:middle line:84%
It pervades everything
in Indian life.

00:45:51.560 --> 00:45:54.120 align:middle line:84%
It's the story of Prince
Rama, the noble Prince

00:45:54.120 --> 00:45:57.270 align:middle line:84%
Rama, and his beautiful
wife, Princess Sita, and how

00:45:57.270 --> 00:45:59.450 align:middle line:84%
they are betrayed
of their kingdom

00:45:59.450 --> 00:46:02.920 align:middle line:84%
and go and spend 14 years
living in the forest.

00:46:02.920 --> 00:46:04.540 align:middle line:84%
And they have a
lovely life there.

00:46:04.540 --> 00:46:10.150 align:middle line:84%
But then she is abducted by a
ten-headed demon called Ravana

00:46:10.150 --> 00:46:15.130 align:middle line:84%
who takes her away and to
Sri Lanka, his kingdom.

00:46:15.130 --> 00:46:21.220 align:middle line:84%
And poor, distraught Rama
gathers armies, his own armies

00:46:21.220 --> 00:46:24.180 align:middle line:84%
and an army of monkeys led
by the glorious Hanuman

00:46:24.180 --> 00:46:25.890 align:middle line:90%
and others.

00:46:25.890 --> 00:46:28.620 align:middle line:84%
And they build a bridge
to Sri Lanka, and they go

00:46:28.620 --> 00:46:30.840 align:middle line:84%
and they, ultimately
after tremendous battles,

00:46:30.840 --> 00:46:31.725 align:middle line:90%
they rescue her.

00:46:31.725 --> 00:46:33.600 align:middle line:84%
Well this is one of the
most beautiful things

00:46:33.600 --> 00:46:34.391 align:middle line:90%
you have ever seen.

00:46:34.391 --> 00:46:38.380 align:middle line:84%
And great costumes and
tremendous, glorious songs.

00:46:38.380 --> 00:46:40.850 align:middle line:90%
And mighty acts.

00:46:40.850 --> 00:46:44.440 align:middle line:84%
And it's one of-- it's just
sheer poetry and glory.

00:46:44.440 --> 00:46:47.430 align:middle line:84%
And I was thinking, oh, I wish
we had something like this.

00:46:47.430 --> 00:46:49.980 align:middle line:84%
When suddenly, the old
Brahmin lady turns to me--

00:46:49.980 --> 00:46:52.790 align:middle line:84%
she's good English--
and she says to me,

00:46:52.790 --> 00:46:54.140 align:middle line:90%
oh, I don't like Princess Sita.

00:46:54.140 --> 00:46:55.290 align:middle line:90%
She is much too passive.

00:46:55.290 --> 00:46:55.530 align:middle line:90%
What?

00:46:55.530 --> 00:46:56.070 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:46:56.070 --> 00:46:58.560 align:middle line:84%
We women in India, we are
much stronger than that.

00:46:58.560 --> 00:47:02.080 align:middle line:84%
We have to change the story--
not make her so passive.

00:47:02.080 --> 00:47:06.269 align:middle line:84%
But madam, the story is at
least 3,000 or 4,000 years old.

00:47:06.269 --> 00:47:06.810 align:middle line:90%
That's right.

00:47:06.810 --> 00:47:07.740 align:middle line:90%
It's very old.

00:47:07.740 --> 00:47:09.650 align:middle line:84%
All the more reason
we have to change it.

00:47:09.650 --> 00:47:11.310 align:middle line:84%
We women in India,
we are strong.

00:47:11.310 --> 00:47:12.640 align:middle line:90%
We are full of purpose.

00:47:12.640 --> 00:47:14.920 align:middle line:84%
We really take
care of everything.

00:47:14.920 --> 00:47:16.670 align:middle line:90%
My name is Sita.

00:47:16.670 --> 00:47:20.050 align:middle line:84%
My husband's name is Rama, same
as there, very common in India.

00:47:20.050 --> 00:47:21.300 align:middle line:90%
He is a lazy bum.

00:47:21.300 --> 00:47:23.210 align:middle line:84%
Anything happen, I'd
have to rescue him.

00:47:23.210 --> 00:47:24.950 align:middle line:90%
We have to change the story.

00:47:24.950 --> 00:47:26.330 align:middle line:90%
Show the strength of women.

00:47:26.330 --> 00:47:27.370 align:middle line:90%
The strength of women.

00:47:27.370 --> 00:47:28.210 align:middle line:90%
Yes, indeed.

00:47:28.210 --> 00:47:31.150 align:middle line:84%
And everybody was
laughing and agreeing.

00:47:31.150 --> 00:47:32.790 align:middle line:90%
And I was so shocked.

00:47:32.790 --> 00:47:35.414 align:middle line:84%
I was watching the
changing of the story.

00:47:35.414 --> 00:47:36.080 align:middle line:90%
Instead of the--

00:47:36.080 --> 00:47:36.913 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right there.

00:47:36.913 --> 00:47:38.840 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: --meak
lady, you know,

00:47:38.840 --> 00:47:42.570 align:middle line:84%
the full, strong, stalwart
partner with the men

00:47:42.570 --> 00:47:44.440 align:middle line:84%
and the whole domain
of the human agenda.

00:47:44.440 --> 00:47:45.190 align:middle line:90%
And there she was.

00:47:45.190 --> 00:47:46.970 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Which really
existed around her.

00:47:46.970 --> 00:47:48.428 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: Which
existed around her

00:47:48.428 --> 00:47:50.652 align:middle line:84%
and which she certainly
was a living advocate of.

00:47:50.652 --> 00:47:51.652 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: A part of, yeah.

00:47:51.652 --> 00:47:55.520 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: Well, you know,
after this glorious, glorious

00:47:55.520 --> 00:47:58.530 align:middle line:84%
presentation, what
follows on the television

00:47:58.530 --> 00:48:01.870 align:middle line:84%
that maybe 300 million
people are watching?

00:48:01.870 --> 00:48:03.070 align:middle line:90%
"Dynasty."

00:48:03.070 --> 00:48:04.546 align:middle line:90%
Downloaded from the satellite.

00:48:04.546 --> 00:48:05.380 align:middle line:90%
"Dynasty."

00:48:05.380 --> 00:48:06.770 align:middle line:90%
I was so embarrassed.

00:48:06.770 --> 00:48:07.770 align:middle line:90%
And the lady, she says--

00:48:07.770 --> 00:48:09.340 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: The American story.

00:48:09.340 --> 00:48:11.140 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: --why
you so embarrassed?

00:48:11.140 --> 00:48:12.570 align:middle line:90%
It is the same story.

00:48:12.570 --> 00:48:13.100 align:middle line:90%
What?

00:48:13.100 --> 00:48:15.558 align:middle line:84%
Yes, you got the good lady,
you got the bad lady, good man,

00:48:15.558 --> 00:48:17.620 align:middle line:84%
bad man, you got the
beautiful clothes.

00:48:17.620 --> 00:48:18.990 align:middle line:90%
People flying through the air.

00:48:18.990 --> 00:48:20.390 align:middle line:90%
Good versus evil.

00:48:20.390 --> 00:48:21.845 align:middle line:84%
Yes, indeed, it
is the same story.

00:48:21.845 --> 00:48:22.345 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:48:22.345 --> 00:48:24.011 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: And she
was absolutely right.

00:48:24.011 --> 00:48:26.400 align:middle line:84%
It was like the world
myth coming together.

00:48:26.400 --> 00:48:27.686 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: In "Dynasty."

00:48:27.686 --> 00:48:28.560 align:middle line:90%
>>HOUSTON: Yes.

00:48:28.560 --> 00:48:34.090 align:middle line:84%
And, you know, it really showed
me that the story is changing.

00:48:34.090 --> 00:48:35.940 align:middle line:84%
When the story is
changing about women,

00:48:35.940 --> 00:48:37.370 align:middle line:90%
it is changing about everything.

00:48:37.370 --> 00:48:38.070 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: This is true, yes.

00:48:38.070 --> 00:48:40.400 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: So it's no longer
the old hero's journey

00:48:40.400 --> 00:48:45.570 align:middle line:84%
with a 16-year-old boy battling
his own toxic problems.

00:48:45.570 --> 00:48:46.410 align:middle line:90%
It is the world.

00:48:46.410 --> 00:48:48.235 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Whisks
away the girl, yes.

00:48:48.235 --> 00:48:49.860 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: It's women
and men together.

00:48:49.860 --> 00:48:53.310 align:middle line:84%
It is people of all ages,
of different ethnic groups,

00:48:53.310 --> 00:48:55.534 align:middle line:84%
as we certainly see
on television today.

00:48:55.534 --> 00:48:56.450 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes, yes, yes.

00:48:56.450 --> 00:48:57.870 align:middle line:90%
>>HOUSTON: It's a world story.

00:48:57.870 --> 00:49:01.400 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So, then, how do
we take that large picture

00:49:01.400 --> 00:49:03.740 align:middle line:84%
and change the
story that we have

00:49:03.740 --> 00:49:07.180 align:middle line:84%
about our past--
about our experiences

00:49:07.180 --> 00:49:09.350 align:middle line:90%
that may have been traumatic?

00:49:09.350 --> 00:49:13.150 align:middle line:90%
How do we change those stories?

00:49:13.150 --> 00:49:15.700 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: One of the ways
that I work in seminars--

00:49:15.700 --> 00:49:19.890 align:middle line:84%
as well as around the world
but also seminars here--

00:49:19.890 --> 00:49:24.120 align:middle line:84%
is I take a great story,
like the "Ramayana,"

00:49:24.120 --> 00:49:26.935 align:middle line:90%
like the life of Gandhi, like--

00:49:26.935 --> 00:49:28.060 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: The life of Christ.

00:49:28.060 --> 00:49:29.601 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: --the
quest for the Grail,

00:49:29.601 --> 00:49:33.440 align:middle line:84%
the life of Christ, the quest
for the Grail, "The Wizard

00:49:33.440 --> 00:49:34.080 align:middle line:90%
of Oz."

00:49:34.080 --> 00:49:36.690 align:middle line:84%
In fact, my next book is
called "The Wizard of Us."

00:49:36.690 --> 00:49:38.280 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, great.

00:49:38.280 --> 00:49:39.920 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: Well, let's take "The
Wizard of Oz" as an example.

00:49:39.920 --> 00:49:40.419 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:49:40.419 --> 00:49:41.340 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:49:41.340 --> 00:49:45.710 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: And what I do is I
have people have experiences

00:49:45.710 --> 00:49:50.120 align:middle line:84%
that follow the trend, the
unfolding of the story,

00:49:50.120 --> 00:49:53.090 align:middle line:84%
but learning different
kinds of things throughout.

00:49:53.090 --> 00:49:55.560 align:middle line:84%
So, for example,
"The Wizard of Oz"

00:49:55.560 --> 00:49:58.476 align:middle line:90%
deals with Dorothy living in--

00:49:58.476 --> 00:49:59.100 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Kansas.

00:49:59.100 --> 00:50:02.530 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: --dustbowl Kansas
in terrible time yearning,

00:50:02.530 --> 00:50:05.810 align:middle line:84%
yearning, somewhere over
the rainbow, yearning.

00:50:05.810 --> 00:50:07.314 align:middle line:90%
You know, she's at a--

00:50:07.314 --> 00:50:08.480 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Skies are blue, yes.

00:50:08.480 --> 00:50:09.850 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: Yes, and
she needs to get out

00:50:09.850 --> 00:50:11.090 align:middle line:90%
of an outmoded situation.

00:50:11.090 --> 00:50:14.140 align:middle line:84%
She goes to her auntie, Auntie
Em, Auntie Em, yearning.

00:50:14.140 --> 00:50:15.520 align:middle line:90%
Oh, go away Dorothy.

00:50:15.520 --> 00:50:17.390 align:middle line:84%
Can't you see we're
counting our chickens?

00:50:17.390 --> 00:50:20.260 align:middle line:84%
You know, the American
way-- counting the chickens.

00:50:20.260 --> 00:50:21.680 align:middle line:84%
And something
awful is happening.

00:50:21.680 --> 00:50:24.949 align:middle line:84%
The naughty-- the dreadful
person, Miss Gulch,

00:50:24.949 --> 00:50:26.740 align:middle line:84%
is going to try to take
away and kill her--

00:50:26.740 --> 00:50:27.085 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Her dog.

00:50:27.085 --> 00:50:27.200 align:middle line:90%
Toto.

00:50:27.200 --> 00:50:28.783 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: --beloved
little dog, Toto.

00:50:28.783 --> 00:50:30.370 align:middle line:90%
Anyway, what happens?

00:50:30.370 --> 00:50:33.620 align:middle line:84%
Where are we in our
lives that we really

00:50:33.620 --> 00:50:35.810 align:middle line:84%
feel we are at the
end of one story

00:50:35.810 --> 00:50:38.830 align:middle line:84%
and we're not at the beginning,
but something in us is calling?

00:50:38.830 --> 00:50:42.860 align:middle line:84%
Something in us is saying,
you are so much more

00:50:42.860 --> 00:50:44.280 align:middle line:90%
and you can be so much more.

00:50:44.280 --> 00:50:46.610 align:middle line:90%
Clearly, you need a journey.

00:50:46.610 --> 00:50:49.800 align:middle line:84%
But often it takes a tornado
or something to shake you up.

00:50:49.800 --> 00:50:50.050 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Something catastrophic.

00:50:50.050 --> 00:50:51.660 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: How have
you been shaken up?

00:50:51.660 --> 00:50:52.450 align:middle line:84%
Well, it doesn't have
to be catastrophic,

00:50:52.450 --> 00:50:53.658 align:middle line:90%
but it's got to shake you up.

00:50:53.658 --> 00:50:54.410 align:middle line:90%


00:50:54.410 --> 00:50:55.620 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Trauma shakes you up.

00:50:55.620 --> 00:50:55.800 align:middle line:90%
>>HOUSTON: Yeah.

00:50:55.800 --> 00:50:56.424 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: A move.

00:50:56.424 --> 00:50:57.720 align:middle line:90%
A death of a loved one.

00:50:57.720 --> 00:50:59.320 align:middle line:90%
>>HOUSTON: Whatever.

00:50:59.320 --> 00:51:00.885 align:middle line:84%
But there's always
there inevitably

00:51:00.885 --> 00:51:03.010 align:middle line:84%
in our lives something
that's going to shake us up.

00:51:03.010 --> 00:51:05.742 align:middle line:84%
Or maybe just abject boredom--
we have got to get out of here.

00:51:05.742 --> 00:51:06.950 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Lack of purpose, yes.

00:51:06.950 --> 00:51:08.075 align:middle line:90%
>>HOUSTON: Lack of purpose.

00:51:08.075 --> 00:51:08.880 align:middle line:90%
Same old, same old.

00:51:08.880 --> 00:51:12.040 align:middle line:84%
Living in serial
monotony, you know.

00:51:12.040 --> 00:51:13.530 align:middle line:90%
So what happens?

00:51:13.530 --> 00:51:15.560 align:middle line:90%
Of course, it is the tornado.

00:51:15.560 --> 00:51:23.790 align:middle line:84%
And in the book-- Frank Baum--
the actual house actually moves

00:51:23.790 --> 00:51:25.970 align:middle line:84%
and then it's a
dream in the movie.

00:51:25.970 --> 00:51:29.917 align:middle line:84%
But she lands in her
creative unconscious.

00:51:29.917 --> 00:51:31.000 align:middle line:90%
Remember it moves out of--

00:51:31.000 --> 00:51:31.480 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yellow brick road.

00:51:31.480 --> 00:51:34.160 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: Yes, and she moves
out of the black and white

00:51:34.160 --> 00:51:36.220 align:middle line:84%
into this colorful
land where she

00:51:36.220 --> 00:51:38.220 align:middle line:90%
meets people who appreciate her.

00:51:38.220 --> 00:51:40.270 align:middle line:84%
That's important, so
I might do something

00:51:40.270 --> 00:51:42.680 align:middle line:84%
about deep appreciation
between people.

00:51:42.680 --> 00:51:45.030 align:middle line:84%
Because there's nothing
better than deep,

00:51:45.030 --> 00:51:49.260 align:middle line:84%
deep seeing appreciation of the
other than to call them forth.

00:51:49.260 --> 00:51:51.280 align:middle line:84%
And she's appreciated
by these little people.

00:51:51.280 --> 00:51:52.780 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So to get
out of your story?

00:51:52.780 --> 00:51:53.446 align:middle line:90%
>>HOUSTON: Yeah.

00:51:53.446 --> 00:51:55.810 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Or like she found
someone who needed more heart.

00:51:55.810 --> 00:51:56.310 align:middle line:90%
>>HOUSTON: That's right.

00:51:56.310 --> 00:51:57.190 align:middle line:84%
Well, we're getting
there, you see.

00:51:57.190 --> 00:51:57.595 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:51:57.595 --> 00:51:58.000 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:51:58.000 --> 00:51:59.625 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: And then
comes the archetype

00:51:59.625 --> 00:52:03.640 align:middle line:84%
of the beloved-- the
great guidance figure--

00:52:03.640 --> 00:52:05.070 align:middle line:90%
Glinda the Good Witch.

00:52:05.070 --> 00:52:07.660 align:middle line:84%
So we get in touch
with a higher self

00:52:07.660 --> 00:52:09.470 align:middle line:84%
that gives us the
higher guidance.

00:52:09.470 --> 00:52:14.020 align:middle line:84%
I call it the intelligy-- the
deep, dynamic, purposeful high

00:52:14.020 --> 00:52:18.370 align:middle line:84%
self that is ourselves as if
we'd had a thousand years to do

00:52:18.370 --> 00:52:21.030 align:middle line:84%
our own development,
our human homework.

00:52:21.030 --> 00:52:21.810 align:middle line:90%
And there she is.

00:52:21.810 --> 00:52:25.400 align:middle line:84%
And she sets her on a new
path, the yellow brick road.

00:52:25.400 --> 00:52:27.032 align:middle line:90%
The road of spiritual pollen.

00:52:27.032 --> 00:52:28.240 align:middle line:90%
Follow the yellow brick road.

00:52:28.240 --> 00:52:29.580 align:middle line:84%
Follow the-- And
who does she meet?

00:52:29.580 --> 00:52:30.621 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Spiritual pollen.

00:52:30.621 --> 00:52:31.490 align:middle line:90%
That's great.

00:52:31.490 --> 00:52:34.380 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: She meets
disempowered parts of herself.

00:52:34.380 --> 00:52:36.410 align:middle line:84%
She meets the
disempowered mind--

00:52:36.410 --> 00:52:39.890 align:middle line:84%
the Scarecrow-- who will
prove during their journey

00:52:39.890 --> 00:52:41.690 align:middle line:90%
to have enormous intelligence.

00:52:41.690 --> 00:52:43.740 align:middle line:84%
So that's where I
may do an exercise

00:52:43.740 --> 00:52:45.590 align:middle line:84%
to activate the
brain in new ways,

00:52:45.590 --> 00:52:49.790 align:middle line:84%
to be able to tap into the
enormous, different kinds

00:52:49.790 --> 00:52:52.710 align:middle line:84%
of resources of different
kinds of intelligence

00:52:52.710 --> 00:52:53.420 align:middle line:90%
that we all have.

00:52:53.420 --> 00:52:53.890 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: There are so many.

00:52:53.890 --> 00:52:55.560 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: So I'll
train people in that.

00:52:55.560 --> 00:52:57.290 align:middle line:84%
Then she meets the
disempowered heart

00:52:57.290 --> 00:52:59.660 align:middle line:84%
in the Tin Man, who
actually turns out

00:52:59.660 --> 00:53:03.170 align:middle line:84%
to be the most sympathetic,
the most radically empathic.

00:53:03.170 --> 00:53:08.020 align:middle line:84%
And we develop heartful
processes and the ability

00:53:08.020 --> 00:53:11.610 align:middle line:84%
to be empathic to others
and to deeply understand,

00:53:11.610 --> 00:53:13.760 align:middle line:84%
to cross the great
divide of otherness,

00:53:13.760 --> 00:53:16.210 align:middle line:84%
to have the compassion
that sees deeply

00:53:16.210 --> 00:53:20.080 align:middle line:84%
into the heart of another as
well as into our own hearts.

00:53:20.080 --> 00:53:21.390 align:middle line:90%
And heal the heart, too.

00:53:21.390 --> 00:53:22.900 align:middle line:90%
We do a lot of healing.

00:53:22.900 --> 00:53:26.030 align:middle line:84%
And then the disempowered
courage in the Cowardly Lion

00:53:26.030 --> 00:53:28.420 align:middle line:84%
who turns out to have-- even
though he may be scared all

00:53:28.420 --> 00:53:31.040 align:middle line:84%
the time, by golly,
he takes the risks.

00:53:31.040 --> 00:53:32.920 align:middle line:90%
He takes the great leaps.

00:53:32.920 --> 00:53:34.510 align:middle line:90%
He carries them on the back.

00:53:34.510 --> 00:53:37.670 align:middle line:84%
He's scared, but by
golly, he does it.

00:53:37.670 --> 00:53:40.770 align:middle line:84%
And how to engender
courage and a passion

00:53:40.770 --> 00:53:42.780 align:middle line:84%
for the possible whereas
before you thought

00:53:42.780 --> 00:53:45.490 align:middle line:84%
you had no passion
at all, you see.

00:53:45.490 --> 00:53:49.280 align:middle line:84%
And then, of course,
ultimately, you face entropy.

00:53:49.280 --> 00:53:50.150 align:middle line:90%
You face evil.

00:53:50.150 --> 00:53:52.310 align:middle line:84%
You face the things,
the breakdown,

00:53:52.310 --> 00:53:55.020 align:middle line:84%
and yet you throw the
water of life on the--

00:53:55.020 --> 00:53:55.820 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Uh-huh.

00:53:55.820 --> 00:53:56.319 align:middle line:90%
In his face.

00:53:56.319 --> 00:53:57.540 align:middle line:90%
>>HOUSTON: Yes.

00:53:57.540 --> 00:53:58.610 align:middle line:90%
And it dissolves.

00:53:58.610 --> 00:54:01.240 align:middle line:84%
And you meet the great wizard
who'd been there all along,

00:54:01.240 --> 00:54:02.840 align:middle line:90%
you know, watching the journey.

00:54:02.840 --> 00:54:06.270 align:middle line:84%
And you discover
that even though he's

00:54:06.270 --> 00:54:09.250 align:middle line:84%
terrifying up there
on the screen,

00:54:09.250 --> 00:54:11.080 align:middle line:84%
the little dog pulls
aside the curtain,

00:54:11.080 --> 00:54:13.470 align:middle line:84%
don't look at that man
behind the curtain.

00:54:13.470 --> 00:54:16.860 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Our greatest demons are
actually small and reduced down

00:54:16.860 --> 00:54:17.620 align:middle line:90%
to--

00:54:17.620 --> 00:54:19.030 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: And it turns
out he's really not

00:54:19.030 --> 00:54:20.404 align:middle line:84%
much of a wizard
at all, but he's

00:54:20.404 --> 00:54:22.570 align:middle line:90%
a very great psychotherapist.

00:54:22.570 --> 00:54:26.290 align:middle line:84%
And he gives them what
they need, you know.

00:54:26.290 --> 00:54:31.870 align:middle line:84%
The beating heart,
the statement that you

00:54:31.870 --> 00:54:36.270 align:middle line:84%
are doctor of thinkology,
the badge that says courage.

00:54:36.270 --> 00:54:38.990 align:middle line:84%
And with her, the fact
that she had the ability

00:54:38.990 --> 00:54:40.190 align:middle line:90%
to return home all the time.

00:54:40.190 --> 00:54:40.930 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: The whole time.

00:54:40.930 --> 00:54:41.971 align:middle line:90%
>>HOUSTON: And the shoes.

00:54:41.971 --> 00:54:45.540 align:middle line:84%
But he had offered to take
her up first of all to Kansas,

00:54:45.540 --> 00:54:47.990 align:middle line:84%
but the dog runs
after a Siamese cat.

00:54:47.990 --> 00:54:51.762 align:middle line:84%
And so she has to
find out from Glinda

00:54:51.762 --> 00:54:54.730 align:middle line:90%
that it was there all the time.

00:54:54.730 --> 00:54:57.180 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And that's basically
what we have in all of us.

00:54:57.180 --> 00:54:57.570 align:middle line:90%
>>HOUSTON: That's what we have.

00:54:57.570 --> 00:54:58.944 align:middle line:84%
And when she gets
home, she says,

00:54:58.944 --> 00:55:01.955 align:middle line:84%
it's in-- I realize it
was in me all the time.

00:55:01.955 --> 00:55:02.970 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: All the time.

00:55:02.970 --> 00:55:04.969 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: And it was the
collective unconscious

00:55:04.969 --> 00:55:07.020 align:middle line:84%
of the human race
that she tunes into.

00:55:07.020 --> 00:55:10.720 align:middle line:84%
We have so much inside
of us all the time.

00:55:10.720 --> 00:55:13.880 align:middle line:84%
And what my work is
about is to help people

00:55:13.880 --> 00:55:17.040 align:middle line:84%
through these activations,
through these exercises,

00:55:17.040 --> 00:55:20.850 align:middle line:84%
to really discover that
we are the wizard, that we

00:55:20.850 --> 00:55:22.050 align:middle line:90%
are the possible human.

00:55:22.050 --> 00:55:25.240 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: To draw that out of
us and to bring that out of us

00:55:25.240 --> 00:55:27.860 align:middle line:84%
in a way that carries
us out of a stuck place.

00:55:27.860 --> 00:55:31.330 align:middle line:84%
But what about when you
feel that that tragedy is

00:55:31.330 --> 00:55:35.050 align:middle line:84%
so concrete, so
disabling, so real?

00:55:35.050 --> 00:55:38.787 align:middle line:84%
You had the experience of
losing your husband of 42--

00:55:38.787 --> 00:55:39.620 align:middle line:90%
>>HOUSTON: 43 years.

00:55:39.620 --> 00:55:40.680 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: --43 years.

00:55:40.680 --> 00:55:41.930 align:middle line:90%
>>HOUSTON: I was well married.

00:55:41.930 --> 00:55:43.055 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Well married.

00:55:43.055 --> 00:55:43.330 align:middle line:90%
>>HOUSTON: Yes.

00:55:43.330 --> 00:55:44.496 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: And happily married.

00:55:44.496 --> 00:55:45.237 align:middle line:90%
>>HOUSTON: Yes.

00:55:45.237 --> 00:55:47.570 align:middle line:84%
With the wonderful ups and
downs that we all go through.

00:55:47.570 --> 00:55:47.990 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Of course.

00:55:47.990 --> 00:55:48.400 align:middle line:90%
That's marriage.

00:55:48.400 --> 00:55:49.200 align:middle line:90%
>>HOUSTON: That's the nature.

00:55:49.200 --> 00:55:50.610 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes, of marriage.

00:55:50.610 --> 00:55:51.940 align:middle line:90%
That's a good distinction.

00:55:51.940 --> 00:55:54.310 align:middle line:84%
But when you went
through that experience--

00:55:54.310 --> 00:55:55.820 align:middle line:90%
and this was not so long ago--

00:55:55.820 --> 00:55:56.900 align:middle line:90%
>>HOUSTON: No, it wasn't.

00:55:56.900 --> 00:55:59.800 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: --how did you
deal with that loss?

00:55:59.800 --> 00:56:02.620 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: Well, I prepared for
it because I knew he was dying.

00:56:02.620 --> 00:56:02.940 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: How do prepare
for something--

00:56:02.940 --> 00:56:04.140 align:middle line:90%
>>HOUSTON: I knew he was dying.

00:56:04.140 --> 00:56:05.920 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But we all
know that eventually--

00:56:05.920 --> 00:56:08.270 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: So what I did
is I sat down with him,

00:56:08.270 --> 00:56:10.820 align:middle line:84%
and I interviewed him
while he lay in bed.

00:56:10.820 --> 00:56:13.950 align:middle line:84%
And I interviewed
him on his life.

00:56:13.950 --> 00:56:15.010 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh my goodness.

00:56:15.010 --> 00:56:15.635 align:middle line:90%
>>HOUSTON: Yes.

00:56:15.635 --> 00:56:19.250 align:middle line:84%
And incidents and things
that-- so that we were together

00:56:19.250 --> 00:56:23.295 align:middle line:84%
in the remembrance and
the harvest of his life.

00:56:23.295 --> 00:56:25.670 align:middle line:84%
And that was a beautiful-- we
did this for several months

00:56:25.670 --> 00:56:26.679 align:middle line:90%
before he died.

00:56:26.679 --> 00:56:27.470 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: As he was--

00:56:27.470 --> 00:56:29.053 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: And that
was very important

00:56:29.053 --> 00:56:33.580 align:middle line:84%
so that we had these deep
times of mutual remembrance.

00:56:33.580 --> 00:56:36.240 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: At any time though,
although you knew he was sick,

00:56:36.240 --> 00:56:39.980 align:middle line:84%
at any time during that
experience did you think

00:56:39.980 --> 00:56:43.020 align:middle line:84%
I can make him live, I can do
this, we can do this together.

00:56:43.020 --> 00:56:43.750 align:middle line:90%
Did you have--

00:56:43.750 --> 00:56:45.420 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: Well, we
did a lot together.

00:56:45.420 --> 00:56:48.040 align:middle line:90%


00:56:48.040 --> 00:56:50.290 align:middle line:84%
But it's became clear
in the last year

00:56:50.290 --> 00:56:54.090 align:middle line:84%
that he-- because he had
congestive heart failure.

00:56:54.090 --> 00:56:57.720 align:middle line:84%
But it was very delicate,
tender, and very beautiful

00:56:57.720 --> 00:56:58.390 align:middle line:90%
time.

00:56:58.390 --> 00:57:01.930 align:middle line:84%
So the very fact that
we completed together--

00:57:01.930 --> 00:57:04.367 align:middle line:84%
do you see it wasn't sudden,
we completed together.

00:57:04.367 --> 00:57:05.200 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Interesting.

00:57:05.200 --> 00:57:07.240 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: It's much more
difficult when it is sudden.

00:57:07.240 --> 00:57:08.073 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's true.

00:57:08.073 --> 00:57:10.295 align:middle line:84%
So you completed together
while he was still alive.

00:57:10.295 --> 00:57:10.920 align:middle line:90%
>>HOUSTON: Yes.

00:57:10.920 --> 00:57:13.200 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And then,
yet, after he was gone

00:57:13.200 --> 00:57:16.150 align:middle line:84%
and his body did
leave this planet,

00:57:16.150 --> 00:57:20.780 align:middle line:84%
do you feel that there's a hole
that still needs filling there?

00:57:20.780 --> 00:57:22.330 align:middle line:90%
Or is it that completion?

00:57:22.330 --> 00:57:23.080 align:middle line:90%
Did it carry over?

00:57:23.080 --> 00:57:23.230 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: Well,
you know what I did?

00:57:23.230 --> 00:57:24.800 align:middle line:90%
He was cremated.

00:57:24.800 --> 00:57:26.940 align:middle line:84%
And I knew he was very
close to ancient Egypt.

00:57:26.940 --> 00:57:32.100 align:middle line:84%
And a month or two after
he died, I went to Egypt.

00:57:32.100 --> 00:57:35.257 align:middle line:84%
And I put his ashes between
the paws of the Sphinx--

00:57:35.257 --> 00:57:36.090 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, you did?

00:57:36.090 --> 00:57:37.820 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: --and
also on the walls

00:57:37.820 --> 00:57:42.260 align:middle line:84%
of an archetype of the Sekhmet
that he was greatly attached to

00:57:42.260 --> 00:57:44.190 align:middle line:90%
and things like that.

00:57:44.190 --> 00:57:48.560 align:middle line:84%
And so I carried him forth
into the next places,

00:57:48.560 --> 00:57:51.720 align:middle line:84%
you see, and had a
sense of his-- well,

00:57:51.720 --> 00:57:53.570 align:middle line:84%
I happen to believe
in continuity.

00:57:53.570 --> 00:57:55.986 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Yes, I was going to
say, do you still communicate?

00:57:55.986 --> 00:57:56.900 align:middle line:90%
>>HOUSTON: I don't.

00:57:56.900 --> 00:58:01.654 align:middle line:84%
It's as if he's moved
on to something else.

00:58:01.654 --> 00:58:03.070 align:middle line:84%
And I'm not
necessarily to give in

00:58:03.070 --> 00:58:04.920 align:middle line:84%
to that kind of--
though people around me

00:58:04.920 --> 00:58:06.680 align:middle line:90%
did have a sense of that.

00:58:06.680 --> 00:58:11.259 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Yes, but you feel more
complete about the entire--

00:58:11.259 --> 00:58:12.050 align:middle line:90%
>>HOUSTON: Oh, yes.

00:58:12.050 --> 00:58:12.360 align:middle line:90%
Oh, yes.

00:58:12.360 --> 00:58:13.095 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: You do.

00:58:13.095 --> 00:58:13.970 align:middle line:90%
>>HOUSTON: Yes, I do.

00:58:13.970 --> 00:58:14.940 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I see that.

00:58:14.940 --> 00:58:16.940 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: But I was
married for 43 years,

00:58:16.940 --> 00:58:18.840 align:middle line:84%
and he was dying
for a year, you see.

00:58:18.840 --> 00:58:19.961 align:middle line:90%
So there was that.

00:58:19.961 --> 00:58:21.460 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But that's
hardly an excuse.

00:58:21.460 --> 00:58:23.310 align:middle line:84%
People are in the situation
of being married for so--

00:58:23.310 --> 00:58:24.310 align:middle line:90%
>>HOUSTON: People-- yes.

00:58:24.310 --> 00:58:25.810 align:middle line:90%
And they feel the hole.

00:58:25.810 --> 00:58:26.330 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:58:26.330 --> 00:58:28.430 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: But we were
filling the hole already.

00:58:28.430 --> 00:58:29.230 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: The whole time.

00:58:29.230 --> 00:58:31.650 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: You know there are
many cultures that do this.

00:58:31.650 --> 00:58:33.470 align:middle line:90%
They prepare for the dying.

00:58:33.470 --> 00:58:35.240 align:middle line:90%
They prepare for it.

00:58:35.240 --> 00:58:38.840 align:middle line:84%
And so by interviewing
him and being

00:58:38.840 --> 00:58:44.440 align:middle line:84%
able to re-live
that life together,

00:58:44.440 --> 00:58:47.310 align:middle line:84%
that we came to the natural
ending and the opening

00:58:47.310 --> 00:58:48.130 align:middle line:90%
to the next stage.

00:58:48.130 --> 00:58:49.796 align:middle line:84%
And we both happen
to believe that there

00:58:49.796 --> 00:58:51.850 align:middle line:84%
was that deep continuity
of one kind or another.

00:58:51.850 --> 00:58:52.516 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Amazing.

00:58:52.516 --> 00:58:57.410 align:middle line:84%
You really do embody the
power of the possible human.

00:58:57.410 --> 00:58:59.610 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: Well, I
struggle at it, you know.

00:58:59.610 --> 00:59:01.992 align:middle line:84%
I keep knocking on the
door of the possibility.

00:59:01.992 --> 00:59:03.950 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, I like that
you say that as well.

00:59:03.950 --> 00:59:06.690 align:middle line:84%
I know that it's-- but
you're humble about it.

00:59:06.690 --> 00:59:08.610 align:middle line:84%
But look what you did
in that experience.

00:59:08.610 --> 00:59:13.650 align:middle line:84%
You embodied the possibilities
that yet our entire culture

00:59:13.650 --> 00:59:16.960 align:middle line:84%
and society has formed
our opinions around death

00:59:16.960 --> 00:59:20.570 align:middle line:84%
being a final,
devastating experience.

00:59:20.570 --> 00:59:23.084 align:middle line:84%
And you preempted it with
something that was filled.

00:59:23.084 --> 00:59:25.000 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: Well, there
was also something else

00:59:25.000 --> 00:59:29.050 align:middle line:84%
that I did that I've never
spoken about publicly.

00:59:29.050 --> 00:59:31.410 align:middle line:84%
He was up at one of
the major birthdays

00:59:31.410 --> 00:59:33.870 align:middle line:84%
just a year or two before--
it was several years

00:59:33.870 --> 00:59:34.740 align:middle line:90%
before he died.

00:59:34.740 --> 00:59:37.640 align:middle line:84%
Major birthday a few
years before he died.

00:59:37.640 --> 00:59:41.662 align:middle line:84%
And I knew it was very important
for him-- this birthday.

00:59:41.662 --> 00:59:43.620 align:middle line:84%
So I said, who would you
like at your birthday?

00:59:43.620 --> 00:59:46.360 align:middle line:84%
And he named all these
people that he admired.

00:59:46.360 --> 00:59:47.830 align:middle line:90%
Margaret Mead.

00:59:47.830 --> 00:59:50.020 align:middle line:90%
Joseph Campbell.

00:59:50.020 --> 00:59:53.230 align:middle line:84%
A man-- a great psychophysical
master-- Feldenkrais.

00:59:53.230 --> 00:59:56.612 align:middle line:84%
Anyway, there were about
a-- oh, Jean Possault.

00:59:56.612 --> 00:59:59.070 align:middle line:84%
Simone de Voiver-- because he
had studied with him in Paris

00:59:59.070 --> 01:00:01.197 align:middle line:90%
when he was a very young man.

01:00:01.197 --> 01:00:03.030 align:middle line:84%
He said, that's who I'd
like at my birthday.

01:00:03.030 --> 01:00:04.420 align:middle line:90%
OK.

01:00:04.420 --> 01:00:06.310 align:middle line:84%
And I didn't tell him
what I was going to do,

01:00:06.310 --> 01:00:10.460 align:middle line:84%
but I got big blow-up
pictures of each one.

01:00:10.460 --> 01:00:11.260 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, great.

01:00:11.260 --> 01:00:13.635 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: And we had a big
table that I put them around.

01:00:13.635 --> 01:00:16.740 align:middle line:84%
And I got little CDs
of their speaking.

01:00:16.740 --> 01:00:18.857 align:middle line:84%
And I put-- I borrowed
everybody's CD--

01:00:18.857 --> 01:00:19.940 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: What a great idea.

01:00:19.940 --> 01:00:22.870 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: And I got
them all so they were all

01:00:22.870 --> 01:00:24.480 align:middle line:90%
talking simultaneously.

01:00:24.480 --> 01:00:26.030 align:middle line:84%
And then-- Bob
didn't know what was

01:00:26.030 --> 01:00:27.910 align:middle line:84%
going on-- I brought
him into his birthday.

01:00:27.910 --> 01:00:30.290 align:middle line:84%
And there were all the people
that he had wanted to have.

01:00:30.290 --> 01:00:30.700 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh my God.

01:00:30.700 --> 01:00:32.110 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: All of
them were dead,

01:00:32.110 --> 01:00:33.462 align:middle line:90%
but there they were alive.

01:00:33.462 --> 01:00:35.170 align:middle line:84%
And they were all
talking simultaneously.

01:00:35.170 --> 01:00:36.170 align:middle line:90%
It was a great birthday.

01:00:36.170 --> 01:00:37.790 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: What a great idea.

01:00:37.790 --> 01:00:39.440 align:middle line:90%
>>HOUSTON: It was great.

01:00:39.440 --> 01:00:41.990 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Those are the types
of nuggets that you remember,

01:00:41.990 --> 01:00:45.120 align:middle line:84%
rather than his passing and the
whole years-- You experienced

01:00:45.120 --> 01:00:48.250 align:middle line:84%
that-- that full
living, that passion.

01:00:48.250 --> 01:00:51.900 align:middle line:84%
When I spoke earlier about the
idea of living with that peace,

01:00:51.900 --> 01:00:53.302 align:middle line:90%
with passion, to living--

01:00:53.302 --> 01:00:54.010 align:middle line:90%
>>HOUSTON: Peace.

01:00:54.010 --> 01:00:58.840 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: --to thrive, living to
a place where we're experiencing

01:00:58.840 --> 01:01:00.710 align:middle line:90%
fullness as human beings.

01:01:00.710 --> 01:01:03.900 align:middle line:84%
There's a clip that I actually
want to share with you of Jean

01:01:03.900 --> 01:01:06.630 align:middle line:90%
speaking at one of her events.

01:01:06.630 --> 01:01:09.300 align:middle line:84%
And this is the energy
that she lives and embodies

01:01:09.300 --> 01:01:11.260 align:middle line:84%
and brings to people
when she speaks.

01:01:11.260 --> 01:01:13.874 align:middle line:90%
Take a look.

01:01:13.874 --> 01:01:14.540 align:middle line:90%
[VIDEO PLAYBACK]

01:01:14.540 --> 01:01:17.050 align:middle line:84%
-You know, we are a very
fortunate group of people.

01:01:17.050 --> 01:01:18.550 align:middle line:90%
We really are.

01:01:18.550 --> 01:01:25.100 align:middle line:84%
Because we have an
extraordinary reason

01:01:25.100 --> 01:01:28.180 align:middle line:84%
for being on earth
in this, the most

01:01:28.180 --> 01:01:30.701 align:middle line:90%
important time in human history.

01:01:30.701 --> 01:01:32.700 align:middle line:84%
Other times thought they
were it, they're wrong.

01:01:32.700 --> 01:01:33.880 align:middle line:90%
This is it.

01:01:33.880 --> 01:01:35.790 align:middle line:90%
This is it.

01:01:35.790 --> 01:01:37.570 align:middle line:84%
The early years of
the new millennium.

01:01:37.570 --> 01:01:40.765 align:middle line:84%
Our job, our holy task,
our great privilege

01:01:40.765 --> 01:01:43.860 align:middle line:90%
is to help to bring about peace.

01:01:43.860 --> 01:01:47.530 align:middle line:84%
Peace that is so rich, so
full of flavor, that it makes

01:01:47.530 --> 01:01:52.160 align:middle line:84%
sense to make peace to shift
the dangerous and fearful

01:01:52.160 --> 01:01:54.670 align:middle line:84%
war-embracing
patterns of century

01:01:54.670 --> 01:01:57.450 align:middle line:84%
to offer a rich and
evocative alternative.

01:01:57.450 --> 01:01:58.010 align:middle line:90%
Yes?

01:01:58.010 --> 01:01:59.490 align:middle line:90%
-Yes.

01:01:59.490 --> 01:02:02.940 align:middle line:84%
-Many years ago I was on a
late-night program-- you know,

01:02:02.940 --> 01:02:03.870 align:middle line:90%
1, 2 o'clock.

01:02:03.870 --> 01:02:05.519 align:middle line:84%
And I don't know
if some of you are

01:02:05.519 --> 01:02:07.560 align:middle line:84%
going to be pushing your
books at 1 and 2 o'clock

01:02:07.560 --> 01:02:09.850 align:middle line:84%
in the morning, but I
tell you what happens

01:02:09.850 --> 01:02:12.890 align:middle line:84%
is after a while
you fall asleep.

01:02:12.890 --> 01:02:15.820 align:middle line:84%
And your mouth keeps
on going, and you're

01:02:15.820 --> 01:02:18.930 align:middle line:84%
sort of stunned at what you
have found yourself saying.

01:02:18.930 --> 01:02:22.100 align:middle line:84%
And what I found
myself saying was

01:02:22.100 --> 01:02:27.340 align:middle line:84%
that many of the images, the
concepts of peace that most

01:02:27.340 --> 01:02:30.230 align:middle line:84%
of us grew up with
is simply too tame.

01:02:30.230 --> 01:02:31.980 align:middle line:90%
Peace should be alluring.

01:02:31.980 --> 01:02:33.160 align:middle line:90%
It should be fascinating.

01:02:33.160 --> 01:02:34.630 align:middle line:90%
It should be challenging.

01:02:34.630 --> 01:02:37.150 align:middle line:84%
In a word, I said,
peace should be sexy.

01:02:37.150 --> 01:02:38.060 align:middle line:90%
[END VIDEO PLAYBACK]

01:02:38.060 --> 01:02:40.320 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Peace should be sexy.

01:02:40.320 --> 01:02:41.000 align:middle line:90%
>>HOUSTON: Yes.

01:02:41.000 --> 01:02:42.120 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Tell me about
peace being sexy.

01:02:42.120 --> 01:02:43.690 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: Well,
it should be sexy.

01:02:43.690 --> 01:02:46.140 align:middle line:84%
Don't let the war
boys hog it all.

01:02:46.140 --> 01:02:47.640 align:middle line:84%
The spit, the spice
and the glamour.

01:02:47.640 --> 01:02:49.130 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: The glamour.

01:02:49.130 --> 01:02:53.130 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: Peace is
your-- mmmm-- your hands

01:02:53.130 --> 01:02:54.910 align:middle line:90%
kneading dough.

01:02:54.910 --> 01:02:58.380 align:middle line:90%
Peace is the walk in the park.

01:02:58.380 --> 01:03:04.480 align:middle line:84%
Peace is little June-- little
ladybugs on white campions.

01:03:04.480 --> 01:03:06.180 align:middle line:90%
Peace is the lovers.

01:03:06.180 --> 01:03:11.350 align:middle line:84%
Peace are the ones
who are like Dorothy

01:03:11.350 --> 01:03:12.780 align:middle line:90%
in that state of yearning.

01:03:12.780 --> 01:03:14.660 align:middle line:90%
Peace is adolescence-busting.

01:03:14.660 --> 01:03:16.940 align:middle line:90%
Peace is great poems.

01:03:16.940 --> 01:03:20.800 align:middle line:90%
Peace is not insipid, dry--

01:03:20.800 --> 01:03:22.540 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Marches and--

01:03:22.540 --> 01:03:24.770 align:middle line:90%
>>HOUSTON: Peace is sexy.

01:03:24.770 --> 01:03:30.550 align:middle line:84%
And that's why we need much
more visceral, vital, sumptuous

01:03:30.550 --> 01:03:33.770 align:middle line:84%
notions of peace, not an
insipid dove-- you know,

01:03:33.770 --> 01:03:34.920 align:middle line:90%
nice as that is.

01:03:34.920 --> 01:03:36.600 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But what
about the activist?

01:03:36.600 --> 01:03:37.960 align:middle line:90%
What about the marches?

01:03:37.960 --> 01:03:39.980 align:middle line:90%
What about the 99%?

01:03:39.980 --> 01:03:41.730 align:middle line:84%
Is that also what
you're talking about?

01:03:41.730 --> 01:03:43.370 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: Yes, it
is taking action.

01:03:43.370 --> 01:03:44.220 align:middle line:90%
It's being there.

01:03:44.220 --> 01:03:47.140 align:middle line:84%
But it's being there not
just being against something.

01:03:47.140 --> 01:03:48.060 align:middle line:90%
It's what you're for.

01:03:48.060 --> 01:03:50.600 align:middle line:90%
It's being in the grand design.

01:03:50.600 --> 01:03:53.840 align:middle line:84%
It's being, as I said, hands-on,
sensory-rich, doing something

01:03:53.840 --> 01:03:54.910 align:middle line:90%
about it.

01:03:54.910 --> 01:03:58.120 align:middle line:84%
And a protest is one part,
but beyond the protest

01:03:58.120 --> 01:03:59.410 align:middle line:90%
is the doing.

01:03:59.410 --> 01:04:03.140 align:middle line:84%
During this whole-- the Occupy
Movement that is going on,

01:04:03.140 --> 01:04:06.110 align:middle line:84%
I was on the phone
often very early

01:04:06.110 --> 01:04:07.610 align:middle line:84%
for different
parts of the world.

01:04:07.610 --> 01:04:09.068 align:middle line:84%
People were calling
me up and said,

01:04:09.068 --> 01:04:12.740 align:middle line:84%
Jean, help us to start to design
the strategy-- what we're for.

01:04:12.740 --> 01:04:15.290 align:middle line:84%
So I would do all kinds
of exercises with people--

01:04:15.290 --> 01:04:18.620 align:middle line:84%
clumps and groups of people--
to design strategies to deepen

01:04:18.620 --> 01:04:22.880 align:middle line:84%
into that great creative process
that's going on all the time

01:04:22.880 --> 01:04:25.730 align:middle line:84%
beneath the surface crust of
consciousness and to come out

01:04:25.730 --> 01:04:30.950 align:middle line:84%
with juicy, feasible, doable,
passionate ideas of things that

01:04:30.950 --> 01:04:33.899 align:middle line:84%
they could do in their
communities to make a--

01:04:33.899 --> 01:04:34.940 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's beautiful.

01:04:34.940 --> 01:04:36.856 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: --more vibrant,
peaceful community.

01:04:36.856 --> 01:04:38.970 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So, for
example, peace has

01:04:38.970 --> 01:04:41.040 align:middle line:84%
to start from
within before it can

01:04:41.040 --> 01:04:44.359 align:middle line:84%
be given an example
outside-- before anything

01:04:44.359 --> 01:04:45.650 align:middle line:90%
can happen outside of our home.

01:04:45.650 --> 01:04:47.358 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: Well, if
you start within it's

01:04:47.358 --> 01:04:50.300 align:middle line:84%
much more likely to be possible
and passionate and doable

01:04:50.300 --> 01:04:50.800 align:middle line:90%
without.

01:04:50.800 --> 01:04:51.560 align:middle line:90%


01:04:51.560 --> 01:04:53.634 align:middle line:84%
Instead of just
saying, let's go!

01:04:53.634 --> 01:04:54.800 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Let's march, please.

01:04:54.800 --> 01:04:55.990 align:middle line:84%
What types of things
would you tell

01:04:55.990 --> 01:04:57.510 align:middle line:84%
people to do in
their communities?

01:04:57.510 --> 01:05:00.240 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: Well, for example,
they would talk to me.

01:05:00.240 --> 01:05:02.670 align:middle line:84%
And different communities
had different issues.

01:05:02.670 --> 01:05:05.610 align:middle line:84%
And they might have
issues around--

01:05:05.610 --> 01:05:06.759 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Violence or--

01:05:06.759 --> 01:05:08.300 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: Well,
not so much violence

01:05:08.300 --> 01:05:10.439 align:middle line:90%
but things going missing.

01:05:10.439 --> 01:05:11.980 align:middle line:84%
The bookstores
closing down, you see.

01:05:11.980 --> 01:05:15.150 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, yes, yes, yes.

01:05:15.150 --> 01:05:18.000 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: Centers for children
to come to after school

01:05:18.000 --> 01:05:20.317 align:middle line:90%
to get back into arts and music.

01:05:20.317 --> 01:05:20.900 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

01:05:20.900 --> 01:05:24.420 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: Places for people
to envision and dream.

01:05:24.420 --> 01:05:25.810 align:middle line:90%
New ideas for the community.

01:05:25.810 --> 01:05:27.320 align:middle line:90%
What could it look like?

01:05:27.320 --> 01:05:29.980 align:middle line:84%
Because when you have a
passionate inner vision,

01:05:29.980 --> 01:05:32.280 align:middle line:84%
when you have the inner
architecture of what

01:05:32.280 --> 01:05:36.360 align:middle line:84%
a community or a family
or a culture can be,

01:05:36.360 --> 01:05:38.200 align:middle line:90%
then things start to move.

01:05:38.200 --> 01:05:41.117 align:middle line:84%
But without the ideas,
things don't tend to happen.

01:05:41.117 --> 01:05:41.700 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

01:05:41.700 --> 01:05:43.880 align:middle line:84%
And so the community
centers and those types

01:05:43.880 --> 01:05:45.710 align:middle line:84%
of things that
reinstated the culture

01:05:45.710 --> 01:05:47.590 align:middle line:84%
was what you brought--
what you taught.

01:05:47.590 --> 01:05:49.048 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: Yes,
among other things.

01:05:49.048 --> 01:05:51.730 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: There's an idea
that you have around

01:05:51.730 --> 01:05:54.530 align:middle line:84%
teaching how to bring about
a person's possibility.

01:05:54.530 --> 01:05:57.290 align:middle line:84%
If you are one of those
people that likes steps

01:05:57.290 --> 01:06:01.910 align:middle line:84%
and how to do things, Jean
teaches about opening yourself

01:06:01.910 --> 01:06:03.820 align:middle line:90%
to limitless possibilities.

01:06:03.820 --> 01:06:06.780 align:middle line:84%
And this is a three-step
process that we kind of

01:06:06.780 --> 01:06:08.250 align:middle line:90%
condensed into three steps.

01:06:08.250 --> 01:06:10.559 align:middle line:84%
But the first of that
is thinking in images.

01:06:10.559 --> 01:06:12.100 align:middle line:84%
We've been doing a
lot of that today.

01:06:12.100 --> 01:06:13.230 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: Well, part of
it yes, that's one of them.

01:06:13.230 --> 01:06:14.770 align:middle line:90%
Thinking in images.

01:06:14.770 --> 01:06:19.370 align:middle line:84%
Making use of the fact that
you are not just a simple ego.

01:06:19.370 --> 01:06:22.400 align:middle line:84%
Ego is but one image among the
multiple images of the psyche.

01:06:22.400 --> 01:06:23.700 align:middle line:90%
You have many people in you.

01:06:23.700 --> 01:06:25.625 align:middle line:90%
For example, if I say who am I?

01:06:25.625 --> 01:06:26.640 align:middle line:90%
I'm a teacher.

01:06:26.640 --> 01:06:28.170 align:middle line:90%
I'm a writer.

01:06:28.170 --> 01:06:29.530 align:middle line:90%
I'm a dog person, big time.

01:06:29.530 --> 01:06:31.520 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: You're a dog lover, yes.

01:06:31.520 --> 01:06:33.330 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: Sometimes
I'm a gardener.

01:06:33.330 --> 01:06:35.740 align:middle line:90%
I'm a traveler, God knows.

01:06:35.740 --> 01:06:38.930 align:middle line:90%
I'm a healer, a meditator.

01:06:38.930 --> 01:06:39.880 align:middle line:90%
I'm a fool.

01:06:39.880 --> 01:06:41.870 align:middle line:90%
I'm a clown, you know.

01:06:41.870 --> 01:06:46.150 align:middle line:84%
I have been an athlete in
earlier parts of my life.

01:06:46.150 --> 01:06:47.430 align:middle line:90%
I love to dance.

01:06:47.430 --> 01:06:50.275 align:middle line:84%
I have all these
different parts of me.

01:06:50.275 --> 01:06:51.650 align:middle line:84%
Now if I were to
say to you, just

01:06:51.650 --> 01:06:54.230 align:middle line:84%
name a stream of consciousness
some of your parts--

01:06:54.230 --> 01:06:58.860 align:middle line:84%
both known and also perhaps not
even-- maybe even further down.

01:06:58.860 --> 01:07:00.110 align:middle line:90%
Name some.

01:07:00.110 --> 01:07:01.220 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I am a mother.

01:07:01.220 --> 01:07:02.580 align:middle line:90%
I am a friend.

01:07:02.580 --> 01:07:04.670 align:middle line:90%
I am a mountain biker.

01:07:04.670 --> 01:07:07.030 align:middle line:90%
I am an orator.

01:07:07.030 --> 01:07:11.050 align:middle line:90%
I am a nature lover.

01:07:11.050 --> 01:07:12.960 align:middle line:90%
I am a healer.

01:07:12.960 --> 01:07:16.377 align:middle line:90%
I am an energy shifter.

01:07:16.377 --> 01:07:16.960 align:middle line:90%
>>HOUSTON: OK.

01:07:16.960 --> 01:07:17.459 align:middle line:90%
Good.

01:07:17.459 --> 01:07:18.170 align:middle line:90%
That's very good.

01:07:18.170 --> 01:07:18.390 align:middle line:90%
Go on.

01:07:18.390 --> 01:07:19.681 align:middle line:90%
The wild cards-- bring them up.

01:07:19.681 --> 01:07:20.890 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

01:07:20.890 --> 01:07:24.900 align:middle line:84%
I am all about the
power of possibilities.

01:07:24.900 --> 01:07:27.510 align:middle line:90%
I am a forward thinker.

01:07:27.510 --> 01:07:31.690 align:middle line:84%
I am all about moving
into the future.

01:07:31.690 --> 01:07:38.610 align:middle line:84%
I am a possible seeker,
and I am a positive person.

01:07:38.610 --> 01:07:39.210 align:middle line:90%
>>HOUSTON: OK.

01:07:39.210 --> 01:07:40.126 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Intentionally.

01:07:40.126 --> 01:07:45.310 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: Now you
see, how do you then

01:07:45.310 --> 01:07:47.860 align:middle line:84%
begin to develop two,
three, four, five,

01:07:47.860 --> 01:07:51.030 align:middle line:84%
or more of these
different persona

01:07:51.030 --> 01:07:52.950 align:middle line:90%
to bring them stage front?

01:07:52.950 --> 01:07:54.850 align:middle line:84%
I'll give it from
my own example.

01:07:54.850 --> 01:07:57.710 align:middle line:90%
I dislike writing intensely.

01:07:57.710 --> 01:07:58.335 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Really?

01:07:58.335 --> 01:07:59.918 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: And I'm
phobic for writing.

01:07:59.918 --> 01:08:01.002 align:middle line:90%
And I have my 27th--

01:08:01.002 --> 01:08:02.050 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: 26th-- 27th book.

01:08:02.050 --> 01:08:03.670 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: Well,
27th is coming up.

01:08:03.670 --> 01:08:07.010 align:middle line:84%
And yet-- and I
have 130,000 pages

01:08:07.010 --> 01:08:09.560 align:middle line:84%
unpublished because
my mystery school

01:08:09.560 --> 01:08:11.290 align:middle line:84%
I had to write a small
book every month.

01:08:11.290 --> 01:08:13.248 align:middle line:84%
And by the time it was
delivered in three days,

01:08:13.248 --> 01:08:14.379 align:middle line:90%
it was 400 pages.

01:08:14.379 --> 01:08:15.920 align:middle line:84%
And this went on
for almost 29 years.

01:08:15.920 --> 01:08:16.779 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, my goodness.

01:08:16.779 --> 01:08:17.479 align:middle line:90%
>>HOUSTON: OK.

01:08:17.479 --> 01:08:20.340 align:middle line:90%
Now what do I do?

01:08:20.340 --> 01:08:24.556 align:middle line:84%
Because I sit down and if Jean
stares at the computer-- blank.

01:08:24.556 --> 01:08:25.930 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It's not
going to happen.

01:08:25.930 --> 01:08:29.364 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: I happen to
be a very good cook.

01:08:29.364 --> 01:08:29.890 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

01:08:29.890 --> 01:08:30.189 align:middle line:90%
Something I didn't realize.

01:08:30.189 --> 01:08:31.980 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: The reason
I'm a very good cook,

01:08:31.980 --> 01:08:34.398 align:middle line:84%
and I'm a serious cook,
is because-- remember

01:08:34.398 --> 01:08:36.189 align:middle line:84%
I talked about my
parents getting divorced.

01:08:36.189 --> 01:08:38.854 align:middle line:84%
Well, earlier when I was
noticing the problems between

01:08:38.854 --> 01:08:41.270 align:middle line:84%
them, my mother-- whose name
was Maria Donciatta Seraphina

01:08:41.270 --> 01:08:45.890 align:middle line:84%
Perpetua you know,
the Gratziella,--

01:08:45.890 --> 01:08:47.304 align:middle line:84%
she was born in
Siracusa, Sicily,

01:08:47.304 --> 01:08:50.220 align:middle line:84%
and she marries Jack
Houston of Texas.

01:08:50.220 --> 01:08:52.684 align:middle line:90%
They hated each other's food.

01:08:52.684 --> 01:08:53.600 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I can imagine.

01:08:53.600 --> 01:08:55.340 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: My father
could not abide

01:08:55.340 --> 01:08:57.029 align:middle line:90%
the smell or look of garlic.

01:08:57.029 --> 01:09:00.740 align:middle line:84%
He would say, Mary, those
things, those are stinkbugs.

01:09:00.740 --> 01:09:02.870 align:middle line:84%
That's what the old witch
ladies down in Texas

01:09:02.870 --> 01:09:04.460 align:middle line:84%
you know they hang
around their neck

01:09:04.460 --> 01:09:05.490 align:middle line:90%
to fight off the run-at-yous.

01:09:05.490 --> 01:09:05.920 align:middle line:90%
No.

01:09:05.920 --> 01:09:07.503 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Where's the
meat and potatoes?

01:09:07.503 --> 01:09:09.140 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: We don't
eat those things.

01:09:09.140 --> 01:09:12.148 align:middle line:84%
Worse than that with
hush puppies and--

01:09:12.148 --> 01:09:13.439 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Southern fried chicken.

01:09:13.439 --> 01:09:14.560 align:middle line:90%
>>HOUSTON: That's right.

01:09:14.560 --> 01:09:18.580 align:middle line:84%
And so what I did to try
to keep them together

01:09:18.580 --> 01:09:20.470 align:middle line:84%
is I became the
world's first fusion

01:09:20.470 --> 01:09:21.590 align:middle line:90%
cook around eight or nine.

01:09:21.590 --> 01:09:24.500 align:middle line:84%
And I would make things
like chicken-fried polenta

01:09:24.500 --> 01:09:28.399 align:middle line:84%
to try to get them-- Anyway,
I became a fusion cook.

01:09:28.399 --> 01:09:30.740 align:middle line:84%
And I stayed, and I
became the family cook.

01:09:30.740 --> 01:09:31.240 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

01:09:31.240 --> 01:09:33.819 align:middle line:90%
>>HOUSTON: And I remain that.

01:09:33.819 --> 01:09:35.489 align:middle line:84%
So that I even had
relatives who would

01:09:35.489 --> 01:09:37.620 align:middle line:84%
come to dinner who had
no idea what else I did.

01:09:37.620 --> 01:09:40.130 align:middle line:84%
They would say, hey, Jean--
especially the Sicilian-- eh,

01:09:40.130 --> 01:09:41.252 align:middle line:90%
she's a cook.

01:09:41.252 --> 01:09:41.960 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, yeah?

01:09:41.960 --> 01:09:42.770 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: And
they once went to--

01:09:42.770 --> 01:09:42.910 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: You're a cook.

01:09:42.910 --> 01:09:44.100 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: --hear me
give a big speech,

01:09:44.100 --> 01:09:45.950 align:middle line:84%
and everybody got
excited by this.

01:09:45.950 --> 01:09:49.000 align:middle line:84%
Hey, Jean, now we thought all
these years all you could do

01:09:49.000 --> 01:09:52.041 align:middle line:84%
was cook, you know,
and you talk good.

01:09:52.041 --> 01:09:53.260 align:middle line:90%
Anyway.

01:09:53.260 --> 01:09:54.640 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

01:09:54.640 --> 01:09:55.570 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

01:09:55.570 --> 01:09:59.040 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: So as a
cook, I am not blocked.

01:09:59.040 --> 01:10:02.696 align:middle line:84%
So when I have to write,
I take on the cook

01:10:02.696 --> 01:10:05.070 align:middle line:84%
or one of the other different
persona that works for me--

01:10:05.070 --> 01:10:05.861 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Archetypes.

01:10:05.861 --> 01:10:09.240 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: --and I find that
I don't have the blocks.

01:10:09.240 --> 01:10:12.590 align:middle line:84%
And I stir in the ideas,
and I add the seasonings

01:10:12.590 --> 01:10:14.100 align:middle line:90%
of different associations.

01:10:14.100 --> 01:10:16.320 align:middle line:84%
And the words begin
to come together.

01:10:16.320 --> 01:10:17.920 align:middle line:90%
And as a cook, I am cooking.

01:10:17.920 --> 01:10:20.381 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: See, I love how
you tie these things in.

01:10:20.381 --> 01:10:22.380 align:middle line:84%
Like how you did earlier
with the visualization,

01:10:22.380 --> 01:10:24.016 align:middle line:90%
you tied that into my goal.

01:10:24.016 --> 01:10:25.890 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: So, for
example, if I were to say,

01:10:25.890 --> 01:10:28.150 align:middle line:84%
of these different
persona-- known

01:10:28.150 --> 01:10:32.840 align:middle line:84%
and also, maybe, latent--
choose one for me right now.

01:10:32.840 --> 01:10:34.330 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: The forward thinker.

01:10:34.330 --> 01:10:34.990 align:middle line:90%
>>HOUSTON: The forward thinker.

01:10:34.990 --> 01:10:35.584 align:middle line:90%
OK.

01:10:35.584 --> 01:10:37.500 align:middle line:84%
Now as a forward thinker,
you are entirely now

01:10:37.500 --> 01:10:38.333 align:middle line:90%
the forward thinker.

01:10:38.333 --> 01:10:39.999 align:middle line:84%
Normally, I would
put on music for you.

01:10:39.999 --> 01:10:40.790 align:middle line:90%
You would dance it.

01:10:40.790 --> 01:10:42.331 align:middle line:84%
You would become
the forward thinker.

01:10:42.331 --> 01:10:45.530 align:middle line:84%
You would walk and act and emote
and be the forward thinker.

01:10:45.530 --> 01:10:46.030 align:middle line:90%
Yes?

01:10:46.030 --> 01:10:46.340 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

01:10:46.340 --> 01:10:47.040 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: And
that's happening now?

01:10:47.040 --> 01:10:48.490 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Yes, I'm
a huge visualizer.

01:10:48.490 --> 01:10:49.073 align:middle line:90%
>>HOUSTON: OK.

01:10:49.073 --> 01:10:51.050 align:middle line:84%
And then visualizer,
forward thinker,

01:10:51.050 --> 01:10:53.690 align:middle line:84%
put yourself in that
family situation

01:10:53.690 --> 01:10:55.110 align:middle line:90%
two or three months from now.

01:10:55.110 --> 01:10:58.670 align:middle line:84%
But entirely not as Lisa
who you know, the ego of you

01:10:58.670 --> 01:11:00.570 align:middle line:90%
Lisa, but as forward thinker.

01:11:00.570 --> 01:11:02.020 align:middle line:90%
Take her and see what happens.

01:11:02.020 --> 01:11:02.672 align:middle line:90%
Now.

01:11:02.672 --> 01:11:04.130 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Take that
to the jump time.

01:11:04.130 --> 01:11:04.810 align:middle line:90%
Take that.

01:11:04.810 --> 01:11:05.790 align:middle line:90%
That's the jump.

01:11:05.790 --> 01:11:08.760 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: Be that, and
be her doing that work

01:11:08.760 --> 01:11:09.760 align:middle line:90%
with your family.

01:11:09.760 --> 01:11:12.660 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And that is--
pretty much I do that a lot.

01:11:12.660 --> 01:11:16.560 align:middle line:84%
When I set a goal, I
go to that-- the end.

01:11:16.560 --> 01:11:18.870 align:middle line:84%
Aren't these many,
many lost modes

01:11:18.870 --> 01:11:22.094 align:middle line:84%
of prayer where this has been
practiced in ancient cultures?

01:11:22.094 --> 01:11:23.010 align:middle line:90%
>>HOUSTON: Absolutely.

01:11:23.010 --> 01:11:25.200 align:middle line:84%
And still are in indigenous
and native cultures.

01:11:25.200 --> 01:11:27.630 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And so it has
since been lost in ours,

01:11:27.630 --> 01:11:31.960 align:middle line:84%
but it's going to that acting
as if it has already happened

01:11:31.960 --> 01:11:34.650 align:middle line:84%
and being in that
place of the cornstalks

01:11:34.650 --> 01:11:38.170 align:middle line:84%
raising up to the armpits in
the deep mud of the rain that

01:11:38.170 --> 01:11:39.990 align:middle line:84%
has fallen in the
middle of a drought.

01:11:39.990 --> 01:11:42.655 align:middle line:84%
And that's where
that feeling comes--

01:11:42.655 --> 01:11:43.530 align:middle line:90%
>>HOUSTON: Very good.

01:11:43.530 --> 01:11:43.770 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: --from.

01:11:43.770 --> 01:11:44.270 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

01:11:44.270 --> 01:11:47.000 align:middle line:84%
That's where I love to
live is in that place

01:11:47.000 --> 01:11:49.384 align:middle line:84%
of possibilities-- no matter
what situation I'm in.

01:11:49.384 --> 01:11:51.550 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: Now look what
just has happened with you.

01:11:51.550 --> 01:11:52.900 align:middle line:90%
Your descriptions have changed.

01:11:52.900 --> 01:11:54.420 align:middle line:90%
Your descriptors have changed.

01:11:54.420 --> 01:11:55.140 align:middle line:90%
They are rich.

01:11:55.140 --> 01:11:55.723 align:middle line:90%
They are full.

01:11:55.723 --> 01:11:56.460 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Colorful.

01:11:56.460 --> 01:11:56.920 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

01:11:56.920 --> 01:11:58.150 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON:They're bu--
And you can feel them.

01:11:58.150 --> 01:11:58.941 align:middle line:90%
You can touch them.

01:11:58.941 --> 01:12:00.260 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes, absolutely.

01:12:00.260 --> 01:12:01.926 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: Because
you've already been--

01:12:01.926 --> 01:12:04.080 align:middle line:90%
you just shifted your persona.

01:12:04.080 --> 01:12:04.970 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: You're right.

01:12:04.970 --> 01:12:06.880 align:middle line:84%
And to live in
that place is what

01:12:06.880 --> 01:12:08.790 align:middle line:90%
the possible human is, right?

01:12:08.790 --> 01:12:10.485 align:middle line:84%
To live in that
energy constantly.

01:12:10.485 --> 01:12:11.174 align:middle line:90%
Filled with--

01:12:11.174 --> 01:12:13.590 align:middle line:84%
>>HOUSTON: Well, not constantly
because you get tired out,

01:12:13.590 --> 01:12:15.450 align:middle line:90%
but when you need it.

01:12:15.450 --> 01:12:18.230 align:middle line:84%
You can pull upon all
these different persona.

01:12:18.230 --> 01:12:22.450 align:middle line:84%
And as you develop them,
then their skillful means,

01:12:22.450 --> 01:12:25.675 align:middle line:84%
their skillful capacities,
can be utilized for anything

01:12:25.675 --> 01:12:26.890 align:middle line:90%
that you wanted.

01:12:26.890 --> 01:12:29.310 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: If you'd like to find
out more about Jean Houston

01:12:29.310 --> 01:12:31.480 align:middle line:84%
and her incredible
body of work, go

